{
  "texts": [
    "It seems that underuse is even twice as frequent as its counterpart [8].",
    "However, there is a bias toward the reduction of overuse in the literature of interventions aimed at improving testing appropriateness.",
    "This may be because of the easier assessment of tests reduction and direct costs savings in reduction of overuse.",
    "In the interventions we reviewed, only one [84] mentioned underuse.",
    "Notably, it was not in accordance with Zhi et al. 's estimations [8], as the results showed an overuse of procalcitonin in one out of five tests, whereas underuse was estimated to occur in one out of 38 tests [84]."
  ]
}